The Beneficent, the Merciful.
Praise be to Allah, the Lord of the worlds.
The Merciful, the Merciful.
The Lord of the Day of Judgment.
We worship Thee, and You ask for help.
Guide us to the straight path.
The path of those whom You have favoured, not of those who have earned Your wrath, nor of those who go astray.
Alif Lam Mim.
This is the Book in which there is no doubt, a guidance for those who fear Allah.
Those who believe in the unseen, and establish prayer and spend out of what We have provided them.
And who believe in what has been revealed to you and what was revealed before you, and they are certain of the Hereafter.
These are on guidance from their Lord, and they are the successful.
Verily, those who disbelieve, it is the same to them whether you warn them or do not warn them, they will not believe.
Allah has set a seal on their hearts and on their hearing, and on their eyes is a covering, and theirs is a great punishment.
Among men are some who say, "We believe in Allah and the Last Day," but they are not believers.
They deceive Allah and those who believe, but they deceive none but themselves, and they perceive not.
In their hearts is a disease, so Allah has increased their disease; and for them is a painful punishment for their lies.
And when it is said to them: Make not mischief on the earth, they say: We are only peacemakers.
Indeed, they are the corrupters, but they do not understand.
And when it is said to them: Believe as the people believe, they say: Shall we believe as the fools believe?
And when they meet those who believe, they say, "We believe"; but when they are alone with their devils, they say, "Indeed, we are with you; we were only mocking."
Allah will mock them, and they will wander in their rebellion in their rebellion.
These are the ones who have purchased error for guidance, so their transaction has no profit, nor are they guided.
Their likeness is like the likeness of one who kindled a fire, and when it had illumined it, Allah took away their light and left them in darkness, so that they cannot see.
Deaf, dumb, blind, and they will not return.
Or like a cloud from the sky, darkness, and lightning, and thunder, and lightning, they thrust their fingers in their ears for fear of death; and Allah encompasses the unbelievers.
The lightning almost takes away their eyes, so when it flashes upon them, they stand in it, and when it comes to them, they stand in it; and if Allah had willed, He could have taken away their hearing and their hearing; surely Allah has power over all things.
O mankind, worship your Lord, Who created you and those before you, that you may become righteous.
Who has made the earth a resting-place for you, and the sky a canopy, and sent down water from the sky, and brought forth fruits for you for your sustenance; then do not set up rivals with Allah; then do not set up rivals with Allah.
And if you are in doubt concerning what We have sent down upon Our servant (Muhammad), then produce a surah (chapter) of the like thereof and call your witnesses (supporters and helpers) besides Allah, if you are truthful.
But if you do it not, and you will never do it, then fear the Fire whose fuel is men and stones, prepared for the disbelievers.
And give glad tidings to those who believe and do good deeds, that they shall have gardens beneath which rivers flow, and they will say, "This is what we were given us before," they will say, "This is what we were given us before," and they will abide therein forever.
Allah is not ashamed of anything but a gnat or a gnat, but those who believe know that it is the truth from their Lord; and those who disbelieve say, "This is what Allah is about to do." And He guides many of them, and He guides many of them, and He guides many the transgressors.
Those who break the covenant of Allah after its break, and sever what Allah has ordered to be joined, and make mischief in the earth; these are the losers.
How can you disbelieve in Allah when you were lifeless and He gave you life, then He will cause you to die, then He will give you life, and then to Him you will be returned.
He it is Who created for you all that is in the earth, then He established the heavens and made them seven heavens, and He has knowledge of all things.
And (remember) when your Lord said to the angels: "I am going to create a vicegerent on earth," they said, "Will you place someone who will cause corruption in it and shed blood, and we will glorify Your Name and sanctify you?"
And He taught Adam all the names, then showed them the angels and said, "Tell me the names of these, if you are truthful."
They said, "Glory be to You, we have no knowledge except what You have taught us. You are the All-Knowing, the All-Wise."
He said, "O Adam, inform them of their names." So when they had informed them their names, He said, "Did I not tell you that I know the secrets of the heavens and the earth, and I know what you conceal and what you reveal?"
And when We said to the angels, "Prostrate yourselves to Adam", they prostrated themselves except Iblis, he refused to be arrogant, and he became arrogant.
And We said: O Adam! dwell thou and thy wife in the Garden, and eat of it wherever ye will, but approach not the approach of this approach, lest ye be of the unjust.
Then Satan made them slip out of it, and made them go out of it, and said, "Go down into the land," and We said, "Go down into the land," and for a time for a while, and for a while, it is a provision for you.
Then learnt Adam from his Lord words of inspiration, and his Lord turned to him; for He is Oft-Returning, Most Merciful.
We said: "Get down all of you all together, and if there comes to you a guidance from Me, then whoever follows My guidance, there shall no fear come upon them neither shall they grieve."
And those who disbelieve and deny Our Signs, they are the companions of the Fire, they shall abide therein forever.
O Children of Israel, remember My favor which I have bestowed upon you, and fulfill My covenant with Me, I will fulfil My covenant with you, and fear Me.
And believe in what I have sent down with you, confirming that which is with you, and be not the first of those who disbelieve, and do not sell My signs for a small price, and fear Me.
And do not mix the truth with falsehood, nor conceal the truth while you know.
Establish prayer and pay the poor-rate and bow down with those who bow down.
Do you enjoin the people with good deeds, and you forget yourselves? When you are the Book, you will not understand.
And seek assistance through patience and prayer, and it is a hard thing except for the humble ones.
Those who know that they will meet their Lord and to Him they will return.
O Children of Israel, remember My favor which I have bestowed upon you, and that I preferred you above all nations.
And fear the Day when no soul will avail another soul, nor will any intercession be accepted from it, nor will compensation be accepted from it, nor will they be helped.
And (remember) when We saved you from Pharaoh's people who were afflicting you with dreadful torment, slaying your sons and sparing your women; and in that was a tremendous trial from your Lord.
And when We parted the sea for you, and saved you and drowned Pharaoh's people while you were looking.
And when We made Moses forty nights, then you took the calf for him, and you were unjust.
Then We pardoned you after that, so that you might be grateful.
And (remember) when We gave Moses the Scripture and the Criterion (between right and wrong), so that you might be guided aright.
And (remember) when Musa said to his people: "O my people! You have wronged yourselves by Allah, so turn to your Lord in repentance and slay yourselves. That is better for you in your own creation. He has mercy on you. He is the All-forgiving, the Most Merciful.
And [mention] when you said, "O Moses, we will not believe in you until we see Allah outright, so the thunderbolt seized you while you were looking."
Then We raised you up after your death, so that you might be grateful.
And We caused you the shade, and We sent down to you manna and quails, saying: Eat of the good things We have provided you; and they did not wrong Us, but they wronged themselves.
And when We said: Enter the city, and eat from it wherever you will, and enter the gate, and say, "Forgive us our sins," and We will forgive you your sins, and We will give you the reward of the righteous.
Then the wrongdoers changed the word of what they had told them, so We sent down upon them a plague from heaven, and We sent down upon them a plague from heaven.
And when Musa prayed for water for his people, We said: Strike your rock with your staff, and then gushed forth from each other; each tribe gushed out of their drinking place; and eat from the sustenance of Allah and do not act on the earth, nor do mischief on earth.
And you said, "O Moses, do not be patient, we will not be patient, so pray for our Lord, the earth, the earth, and the birds, and the birds, and the birds, and the birds, which We have created for us." They will be told, "What is the matter with you?" And they were afflicted with the cause of Allah, and they were afflicted with the cause of Allah. They were in the midst of those who did not believe in Allah and all that they had done. They were in the midst of those who did not believe in Allah, and they were transgressors.
Those who believe, and those who are Jews, and the Christians, and the Sabians, whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day and does good, they shall have their reward with their Lord, and no fear shall come upon them, nor shall they grieve.
And when We took a covenant with you and raised the Mount above you, saying: Hold fast to what We have given you, and remember that which is in it, so that you may fear Allah.
Then you turned away after that, and it was not for the grace of Allah upon you and His mercy.
And you know those of you who transgressed concerning the Sabbath, so We said to them, "Be apes, despised."
So We made it a lesson for the towns and those who lived in the towns, and a reminder for those who fear Allah.
And when Moses said to his people, "Indeed, Allah commands you to sacrifice a cow." They said, "Are you mocking us?" He said, "Indeed, I am of the ignorant."
They said, "Call upon us your Lord to make plain to us what it is." Moses said, "He is a cow, neither a son, nor a young man." So do you have what you were commanded? So do you have what you were commanded?
They said: Call upon your Lord for us to make plain to us its colour. He said, "This is a cow," she said, "It is a cow whose colour is white."
They said, "Call upon your Lord for us that He may make it clear to us what she is like us. If Allah wills, we will surely be guided."
He said, "It is he who has a cow, he has no ground on the earth, nor does any of the water, nor does he eat any food." They said, "We have come to you." They said, "I have come to you." They will not be able to do anything.
And when you killed a man, and disputed with you, and Allah was with what you were hiding.
So We said: Strike the dead with a part of it, and Allah will bring the dead to life, and He will show you His signs, so that you may understand.
Then, after that, your hearts are hardened, even though they are stones, even though they are rocks, and there are some of them that gush forth from the ground, and there are some of them who are covered with water, and there are some of them who fear Allah. And Allah is not unaware of what you do.
“Do you think that you should believe in Him while a group of them heard the word of Allah, then they understood it, and they understood it knowingly?”
And when they meet those who believe, they say, "We believe"; but when they meet each other with each other, they say, "Do you tell them what Allah has revealed to you, that they may argue with you concerning what Allah has revealed to you?"
Do they not know that Allah knows what they conceal and what they reveal?
And among them are those who do not know the Book but the Book, and they do not know except what they are doing.
So woe to those who write their hands in the Book, and they will say, "This is from Allah," so that they may take a small price for it; so woe to them for what their hands have earned, and woe to them for what they earn.
And they say: "The Fire will not touch us but for a few numbered days." Say: "Have you taken a covenant from Allah, that Allah will not fail His promise, or do you say about Allah what you do not know?"
Nay, those who do evil and do evil deeds, these are the inmates of the Fire; they shall abide therein forever.
As for those who believe and do good works, they are the dwellers of Paradise, they will abide therein forever.
And (remember) when We took a covenant from the Children of Israel (saying): "Worship none but Allah, and be dutiful to parents, and to the orphans, and to the orphans, and to the orphans, and to speak to the people, and to speak the prayer, and to establish the prayer, and to pay the poor-rate."
And (remember) when We took a covenant with you (O Muhammad SAW): “Do not shed your blood, nor will you take your homes out of your homes, and you will be witnesses, and you will be witnesses.”
Then you will be the people of your people, and from his people a group of the wicked, and a group of the wicked, and some of them are one of them, and some of them are in the midst of you, and they will not leave you with what they have eaten with you. And the punishment of the Day of Resurrection will come to you, and you will be in the torment of the Day of Resurrection. And Allah is not unaware of what you do.
They are the ones who bought the life of this world for the Hereafter, so their punishment will not be lightened, nor will they be helped.
And certainly We gave Moses the Book and followed after him messengers; and We gave Jesus the son of Mary, clear arguments, and strengthened him with the Holy Spirit.
And they say: Our hearts are hearts. Nay, but Allah has cursed them for their disbelief, even though they believe.
And when they had received the Book from Allah, confirming that which was with them before them, and before the disbelievers had come to them, they refused to disbelieve in it, and when it came to them, they disbelieve in it; then the curse of Allah is upon those who disbelieve.
Evil is that which they have sold in that which Allah has sent down, that they may disbelieve in that which Allah has sent down from among His servants; so they have incurred wrath with wrath, and wrath has afflicted them with wrath; and for the unbelievers is a disgraceful punishment.
And when it is said to them: Believe in what Allah has sent down, they say: We believe in what was sent down to us, and they disbelieve in what was sent down to us.
And indeed Moses came to you with clear proofs, then you worshipped the calf, and you were unjust.
And (remember) when We took a covenant from you and raised the Mount above you, (saying): Hold fast to what We have given you and listen to it, and they said, "We hear and we do not believe," and their hearts took the calf for their disbelief. Say: "What is it that you believe?"
Say: "If the abode of the Hereafter with Allah is specially for you and the other people, then wish for death, if you are truthful."
And they will never wish for that which their hands have sent before, and Allah is well aware of the unjust.
And thou wilt find them in the life of the people, and the idolaters are more than the idolaters; each one of them desire a thousand years; and it is not for him to save him from the punishment of the punishment. And Allah is Seeing of what they do.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Whoever is an enemy to Gabriel (Gabriel), then he is the enemy of Allah to your heart, confirming that which was before it, confirming that which was before it, and a guidance and glad tidings for the believers."
Whoever is an enemy to Allah and His angels and His Messengers and Gabriel, then surely Allah is an enemy to the disbelievers.
We have sent down to you clear signs, and none will deny them except those who disbelieve.
And if they had heard a covenant, a party of them would not believe.
And when a Messenger comes to them from Allah, confirming what was with them, a party of those who were given the Book threw the Book of Allah behind their backs as if they were unaware.
And those who were in the footsteps of those who had gone down before him were cast down into the devils, and it became Satan, the devil, the devil, the devils, the people of the world, and they were the ones who were in the midst of themselves, and they were not in the presence of the people, and they were in the midst of themselves. And they were not in the presence of those who had been given the truth. And if they had made a lie, they would not be able to destroy them. And if they had made a lie, they would not be able to destroy them.
And if they had believed and feared Allah, it would have been better for them, if they had known.
O you who believe! do not say, “Do not say, ‘Do not say,’ and say, ‘Listen and listen.’ And the unbelievers have a painful punishment.
The People of the Book and the People of the Book will not take any good for you from your Lord. And Allah chooses for His mercy whom He wills, and Allah is the Owner of great bounty.
Do We abrogate a verse or cause it to be forgotten, then We bring a better one or similar to it? Do you not know that Allah has power over all things?
Do you not know that the kingdom of the heavens and the earth belongs to Allah, and that you have no protector or helper?
Or do you ask your Messenger to question Moses before he had been questioned? He who changeth unbelief for a believer has strayed from the right path.
Many of the People of the Book wish that they would turn away from you after your belief after the truth has become clear to them, even after the truth has become clear to them, and forgive and overlook; for Allah has power over all things.
And keep up prayer and pay the poor-rate, and whatever good you send before you, you will find it with God; surely Allah sees what you do.
They say: "None shall enter Paradise unless he be a Jew or a Christian." They are their own desires: Say: "Bring your proof if you are truthful."
Nay, but whoever submits his whole self to Allah and is a doer of good, he will have his reward with his Lord; on them shall be no fear, nor shall they grieve.
And the Jews say, "The Christians are nothing but the Christians," and the Christians say, "The Jews have nothing to follow," although they recite the Book, but they do not know what they say.
