And the Jews will not be pleased with you, nor will the Christians be with you until you follow their creed. Say, "The guidance of Allah is the guidance." And if you follow their desires, then you will have no protector or helper.
Those to whom We have given the Book recite it, as it is written in it; they believe in it, and whoever disbelieves in it, they are the losers.
O Children of Israel, remember My favor which I have bestowed upon you, and that I preferred you above the nations.
And guard yourselves against a day when no soul will avail another, nor will compensation be accepted from him, nor will any intercession be taken out from any of them, nor will they be helped.
And (remember) when Ibrahim (Abraham) tried his Lord with certain words, and he fulfilled it, and said: "I am going to appoint a place for you (O Muhammad)," he said, "I am going to make a covenant with you."
