And those who take their religion as a sport and sport, and give them the life of this world, and warn them of the life of this world; but if they do not have any protector, they will not have any protector, nor shall they have any protector, nor shall they have any protector.
Say: "Shall we worship besides Allah that which gives us no profit, nor will He harm us, and then He will have guided us to the right path, even though they turn away from the Shaitan, and that they may turn away from the evil way in the land?" They will call out to Allah, the Lord of the worlds. Say: "This is the guidance of Allah, and we have been commanded to obey the Lord of the worlds."
“And keep up prayer, and fear Him, and He will be to you all together.”
And He it is Who created the heavens and the earth in truth; and on the day He will say, "Be!" and it will be said to him: "This is the truth," and on the Day when the trumpet will be blown, His will be the kingdom of the unseen; and He is the Wise, the Wise.
When Abraham said to his father Azar, "Do you take idols for idols? I will see you and your people in manifest error."
Thus did We show Abraham the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, that he might be of those who believe.
And when the night saw him, he saw a star, and he said, "This is my Lord." But when it came, he said, "I do not love the truth."
And when he saw the moon rising, he said, "This is my Lord," but when it set, he said, "Unless my Lord guides me, I will surely be among the people of the people."
And when he saw the sun rising, he said: This is my Lord, this is greater than this; but when it set, he said, "O my people, I am quit of you."
Verily, I have turned my face to Him who created the heavens and the earth, and I am not of the polytheists, and I am not of the polytheists.
And his people disputed with him, saying, "Do you dispute with me about Allah, when He guided me to the right path? I fear no fear of what you associate with Him. My Lord comprehends all things in knowledge. Will you not remember?"
How should I fear that which you associate with Him, when you fear not that you have associated with Allah what He has sent down to you? But if you know what is better, then the two parties will be better than the two.
Those who believe, and do not believe in their belief, for them are those who are secure and are guided.
And this is Our argument which We gave Abraham to his people. We raise in degrees whomever We please; surely your Lord is Wise, Knowing.
And We gave Abraham Isaac and Jacob, all of them We guided before Noah, and of his progeny, and to David and Solomon, and Job, and Joseph, and Moses, and Moses, and Moses, and Moses. Thus do We reward the righteous.
And Zakariya (Zachariya), and Yahya (Jesus), and Isa (Jesus), and Elias (Jesus), each one of them was among the righteous.
And Ishmael, Elisha, and Lot, and each one of them We preferred above the nations.
And of their fathers and their offspring, and of their brothers, and We guided them and guided them to a straight path.
That is the guidance of Allah, He guides whom He wills of His servants, and if they associate others with Him, they would have been destroyed.
These are the ones who gave the Book to the Book and the wisdom and the Prophethood; but if they disbelieve in it, We have a people who disbelieve in it.
They are those whom Allah has guided, so follow their guidance; Say: I do not ask any reward for you; this is a reminder for the worlds.
And they did not take the covenant of Allah with him, because they said: "Allah has sent down all that He has sent down to us." Say: "Why did He not send down the Book (of the Qur'an) which He has revealed to you, and the guidance (of the Qur'an)?" And you will not be able to make it clear to the people, and that you may make clear that which you are hiding with. Say: "This is Allah's Book." Say: "It is Allah Who has sent down the Book, and what is in your hearts."
And this is the Book which We have revealed to it, verifying that which is before it, and that you may warn the Mother of Cities and those around it, and those who believe in the Hereafter believe in it, and they are their prayers.
And who is more unjust than he who forges a lie against Allah or says, "It has been revealed to me," and he has not been revealed to him, or is not revealed to him; or if you see it, the angels will be placed on their faces, and the angels will be placed on their faces, and the angels will say, "I am the Book of the Book." And if you see it, then the angels will be with you, and you will be the arrogant.
And indeed you have come to Us, as We created you first, and you have left behind your backs, and We have not seen you with your intercessors, and We do not see with your intercessors those whom you asserted that you were partners with those whom you asserted.
It is Allah Who splits the seed and the date-stone, the living, the living, the living from the living. That is Allah, the Creator of the living; so how are you turned away?
He is the One Who breaks the day, and the night, and the sun, and the sun, and the moon for reckoning; it is He Who is the Mighty, the Knowing.
And He it is Who has made the stars subservient to you, so that you may be guided by the darkness of the sea and the sea; indeed We have explained signs for people who know.
And He it is Who has created you from a single soul, then there is a place of a resting-place and a place of years, and We have explained signs for people who understand.
And He it is Who sends down water from the sky, then We bring forth with it all kinds of fruits, and We bring forth from it the fruits of which We bring forth the clusters of palm-palms, palm-trees, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and olives and pomegranates, when they see its fruit. Surely there are signs in this for those who believe.
And they associate the jinn with Allah, while He has created them, and they attribute to Him sons and daughters; glory be to Him, and He is above what they do.
Who is the Creator of the heavens and the earth? How can He have a son, and He has no consort, and He created all things, and He has knowledge of all things?
Such is Allah, your Lord; there is no god but He, the Creator of all things; so worship Him.
His eyes cannot comprehend Him; He comprehends all things; He is the Subtle, the Aware.
Indeed, there has come to you clear proofs from your Lord; so whoever sees, it is for his own soul, and whoever goes blind, it is to his own loss; and I am not a guardian over you.
And thus do We explain the revelations (of the Qur'an) in order that they may say, "You have studied," and that We may make it clear to a people who know.
Follow what has been revealed to you from your Lord; there is no god except Him, and turn away from the polytheists.
And if Allah had pleased, they would not have associated with Him, but We have not made you a guardian over them, nor are you a guardian over them.
Do not insult those whom they call upon besides Allah, lest they insult Allah wrongfully. Thus We have made their deeds fair-seeming to each of them, and to their Lord is their return, then they will be returned to their Lord, He will inform them of what they did.
And they swear by Allah with their strongest oaths, that if a sign comes to them, they would believe in it. Say: "Signs are with Allah." But if they had believed, they would not believe.
And We will turn their hearts and their eyes, and they will not believe in the first time, and We will leave them in their rebellion in distraction.
And if We sent down to them angels, and the dead had spoken to them, and We had gathered all things before them, they would not believe unless Allah willed, but most of them are ignorant.
And thus We have made every prophet an enemy of the jinn and the jinn, but they inspire each other with specious speech, and if your Lord had willed, they would not have done it.
And that the hearts of those who do not believe in the Hereafter may incline to it, and that they may be pleased with it, and that they may do what they are doing.
Say, "Shall I seek other than Allah as a judge, when He has revealed to you the Book? Those who have been given the Book know that it has been revealed to you from your Lord. So do not be among the doubters."
And the word of your Lord is true in truth and in justice; none can change His words; and He is the Hearing, the Knowing.
And if you obey most of those on earth, they will mislead you from Allah's way.
Surely your Lord knows best who has strayed from His path, and He knows best those who are guided.
If you believe in God, then you will be in His name.
And what aileth you that you do not eat in the name of Allah, when He has made clear to you what He has forbidden you to err? But many of them follow their low desires. But most surely many of them follow their low desires. Surely your Lord knows best the transgressors.
And forgive the sin of the past and the open, for those who commit sins will be recompensed for what they have done.
And do not eat anything of the mention of Allah's name, and that it is a sin that is most hateful to them, and the Satans inspire you to argue with them, and if you obey them, then you are polytheists.
Is he who We gave life to him, and We made him light in the light, like he who walks in the way of men, like he who is in the darkness of the blind? Thus does those who disbelieve do what they do.
And thus We have made the criminals leaders of the criminals, in order that they might plot therein, but they do not plot except except themselves, and they do not know.
And when a sign comes to them, they say, "We will not believe until we have been given the Messengers of Allah." But Allah knows best what is given to His servants, and the punishment of those who have done evil will have a severe punishment from Allah, and a severe punishment will befall them.
And whomsoever Allah wills to guide, He opens his breast to Islam, and whomsoever He wills to go astray, He makes his breast narrow and constricted as if he were climbing as though he were climbing.
This is the straight path of your Lord. We have explained the signs for a people who remember.
They will be the home of Paradise with their Lord, and He will be their guardian.
On the day when He will gather them all together, He will say, "O you assembly of jinn, many of you are the jinn and the people, and the people will say, 'Our Lord, we have given some of us a good thing, so that you will be the first of those who have been given us.' He will say, "Your refuge is the Fire. Your Lord is Wise and Knowing."
Thus do We make the wrongdoers a part of what they used to earn.
O assembly of jinn and men, did not the Messengers come to you from among you, reciting to you My signs and warning you of the meeting of this Day of yours? They will say, "We bear witness against ourselves, and the life of this world has come to you." They will bear witness against themselves, and they will bear witness against themselves.
That is because your Lord would not destroy the towns unjustly while their people were unaware.
And they are degrees of what they do, and your Lord is not unmindful of what they do.
And your Lord is the Self-sufficient, the All-Merciful, and if He wills, He will destroy you, and after you will He raise your successors, even as He raised you up from the other people.
Verily, the promise which you are promised will surely come to you, and you will not escape.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "O my people! Work according to your deeds, and I am acting on the (right) work; but you will know that the reward of the Hereafter will be the end of the Hereafter; surely the unjust will not prosper."
And they assign to Allah a share of that which He has created for them, and of what He has created, and they say, "This is for Allah," and they say, "This is for Allah." But what they associate with Allah, they will not reach their associates, and what they associate with Allah is what they do.
And indeed, many of the idolaters have made their children fair-seeming to their children, so that they may ruin them and make their religion obscure to them; and if Allah had willed, they would not have done it. So leave them with what they fabricate, and leave them with what they fabricate.
And they say, "We eat the crops and the crops and the crops, except that they may not eat except what they please, and they will say, 'There is forbidden for them the forbidden cattle,' and they do not mention Allah's name, for they are liars.
And they say: "What is in the bellies of the cattle is that which is in the bellies of our males, and for our women is forbidden; but if they die, they shall be in all that is in it. He will punish them for their sins; surely Allah is All-Knowing, All-Knowing."
Those who kill their children wrongfully, without knowledge, and forbid what Allah has provided for them, they invent a lie against Allah, and they have gone astray, and they are not guided.
And He it is Who produces the gardens and the trees, and the crops, and the crops, and the crops, and the olive, and the olive, and the leaf, and the stars, and the fruit thereof, and the fruit of the day, and the harvest of the day; and do not be excessive, for Allah loves not the transgressors.
And of the cattle and the earth, and some of the earth. Eat of what Allah has provided for you, and do not follow the footsteps of Satan; surely he is your open enemy.
[28.88] Eight are the pairs of the birds, and of the goats, and of the goats, and the two of them, or the females, or the females, or the two females, if you are truthful, if you are truthful.
And of the camels and of the camels. Say: "Is this the two males, or the two females, or the two females, or the wombs of the wombs of the two females?" And when Allah spoke to you, you could be more unjust than one who invents a lie against Allah. And who is more unjust than he who invents a lie against Allah, and who is more unjust than he who does not guide the unjust people?
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "I do not find any forbidden in what has been revealed to me (i.e. the Qur'an) which has been revealed to me except that which is forbidden for death, or the blood of swine, or the blood of swine, or the flesh of swine." But whoever is forced by necessity, without wilful disobedience, nor transgressing it, then surely your Lord is Forgiving, Merciful.
And We forbade the People of the Jews all kinds of fat, and We forbade them the fat of their fat, or the fat of their fat, or the entrails, or the entrails, except that which We have prepared for them. We have punished them with their deeds, and We are the truthful.
And if they deny you, say: "Your Lord is the Owner of Mercy, and His punishment will not be averted from the guilty people."
The idolaters will say, "Had Allah willed, we would not have associated anything with Him, nor did we have any other gods but He." Likewise, those who lived before them were liars, until they tasted Our punishment. Say, "This is a sign with you. You only follow it."
Say, "Allah is the conclusive argument. Had He willed, He would have guided you all.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Say to those who bear witness of their witness (i.e. the Qur'an), and if they bear witness that they do not bear witness with them, and do not bear witness with them (the Qur'an), those who reject Our communications and those who do not believe in the Hereafter do not say to those who reject Our Signs and do not believe in the Hereafter."
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "I have been forbidden to reveal to you what you have been forbidden by your Lord, so do not associate anything with Him, and do not kill your children, nor kill your children. Do not kill your children, and do not take the weight of what you do.
And do not approach the orphan with the best of the best, until he attains its maturity, and give full measure and justice, and do not bear the burden of any man beyond its capacity. And when you speak, be fair, if you speak. And Allah has given you the covenant, that you may remember.
"And verily, this is My Straight Path, so follow it, and do not follow other ways, for they will separate you away from His path.
So We gave Moses the Book, complete to those who do good, and a detailed explanation of all things, and a guidance and a mercy, that they may believe in the meeting with their Lord.
And this is a blessed Book which We have revealed to you, so follow it and fear that you may receive mercy.
Lest you should say, "The Book was sent down to two communities before us, and we were unaware of what we were unaware of."
Or lest you should say, "If the Book had been sent down to us, we would surely have followed it better than they had been guided. There has come to you a clear proof from your Lord, and a guidance from your Lord. Who is more unjust than he who rejects the signs of Allah and turns away from them? We have prepared for those who turn away from Our signs, for the punishment of Our signs."
Do they wait until the angels come to them, or from your Lord, or from your Lord, or from your Lord? On the Day when the sign of your Lord will come, a man will not believe, nor will he believe. Say: "Wait for us." Say, "Wait, and wait." Say: "Wait, and wait."
Those who divide their religion and break into sects, you have no concern with them. Their affair is with Allah, and He will inform them of what they did.
He who brings a good deed will receive the like thereof, and whoever does evil, it will be recompensed with him, and they will not be wronged, and they will not be wronged.
Say, "Indeed, my Lord has guided me to a straight path, the upright, the upright, the upright, the upright."
Say: "Verily, my prayer, my sacrifice, my living and my dying are for Allah, the Lord of the worlds.
There is no associate with Him, and I am commanded to be the first of those who submit to Him.
Say, "Shall I seek other than Allah as a Lord? And He is the Lord of all things, and every soul will bear no burden except by the burden of another; and no bearer of burden shall bear another burden from the burden of your Lord.
And He it is Who has made you successors in the earth, and He has raised you in ranks above others, that He may try you in what He has given you; surely your Lord is swift in retribution; surely He is Forgiving, Merciful.
Alif-Lam-Meem.
The Book has been sent down to you, so let not your breast be hasty in your breast, so that you may warn it, and a reminder for the believers.
Follow what has been revealed to you from your Lord, and do not follow any other guardians except Him. Little are the little ones.
And how many a town have We destroyed, so Our punishment came to them in the night or in the evening they were sleeping.
When Our punishment came to them, their cry was only to say, "We were unjust."
Then We will question those to whom the Messengers were sent, and We will surely question the Messengers.
Then We will narrate to them with knowledge, and we were not absent.
On that day the truth will be true, and those whose scales are heavy will be successful.
And as for those whose scale is light, they are those who have lost their own souls because they deny Our signs.
And We have established you in the earth and made it for you in the earth; little are you grateful.
We created you, then fashioned you, then We said to the angels, "Prostrate to Adam", and they prostrated themselves except Iblis, he refused to be of those who prostrated.
He said, "What prevented you from what you used to do?" He said, "I am better than I, and I have created you from fire, and You created him from clay."
He said, "Get down from the sky, so do not be arrogant, for you are not arrogant.
He said, "Allow me respite until the Day of Resurrection."
He said, "You are of the reprieved."
He said, "You have led me astray, for I will wait for them in the way of men."
Then I will come to them from before them and from behind them, and from their right and from their left, and You will not find most of them grateful.”
He said, "Get away from the heaven, outcast, and whoever will follow you, I will fill Hell with you all together."
"O Adam! dwell thou and thy wife in Paradise, and eat from wherever ye please; but approach not the approach of this, lest ye be of the unjust."
Then Satan whispered to them that He might test them with what was hidden from them of their shame, and he said, "Your Lord only forbade you this tree, lest you should become angels or become immortal."
And he swore to them, saying: Verily, I am your sincere adviser.
So he made them slip by deceit, so when they tasted the tree, their shame became clear to them, and they began to cover themselves with the Garden of Eden, saying, "Did I not forbid you what I did not forbid you?" And their Lord said to them, "Indeed, Satan is an enemy to you."
They said, "Our Lord, we have wronged ourselves, and if You do not forgive us and have mercy on us, we will surely be of the losers."
(Allah) said: "Go ye forth in the land with one another, and for you is the abode of the earth, and a provision for a time."
He said, "Therein you will live, and therein you will die, and from it you will be brought forth."
O children of Adam! We have sent down to you a garment of clothing, and a garment of beauty, and the garment of piety, and the piety of the righteous; this is the best of the signs, so that they may remember.
O children of Adam, let not Satan seduce you, as he got your parents out of the Garden, stripping them of their raiment, to expose them to their shame; and he and his tribe see you, you see them; We have made the devils friends for those who believe.
And when they commit an indecency, they say: "We found our fathers doing it," and Allah commanded us what is commanded to us; Say: "Verily, Allah does not command indecency.
Say, "My Lord has commanded justice, and that you stand on your faces at every place of worship, and call upon Him in sincere devotion, and you will not be able to worship Him as He created you, so you will return."
He has guided the people, and some of them have deserved error. They have taken the devils as protectors instead of Allah, and they think that they are guided.
O children of Adam, eat your prayer at every time of prayer, and eat and drink, but do not be excessive; surely Allah does not love the transgressors.
Say: "Who has forbidden the adornment of Allah which He has produced for His servants and the good things?" Say: "They are the ones who are in the life of this world, on the Day of Resurrection, on the Day of Resurrection. Thus do We explain the Signs for those who understand."
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "My Lord has only forbidden immoralities (indecencies), the apparent of them, and all that is hidden, and sin, and oppression, and wrong-doing, and that you associate with Allah that for which He has not sent down authority, and that you say concerning Allah what you do not know."
And for every nation is a term appointed; so when their term comes, they will not be able to delay a single hour, nor will they advance.
O children of Adam, if there come to you messengers from among you, rehearsing My revelations to you, then whoever practices piety and reforms, there shall no fear come upon them neither shall they grieve.
And those who deny Our signs and treat them with arrogance, these are the inmates of the Fire, they shall abide therein forever.
Who is more unjust than he who invents a lie against Allah or rejects His signs, even though they are in the Book, and when Our angels will say, "Where are those whom you call upon besides Allah?" They will say, "Where you call upon besides Allah," they will say, "This is our Lord," they will bear witness against that which they were denying.
He will say, "Enter into the Fire with the Fire and the people who were before you." And when a group of them will be thrown into the midst of the people, when they will enter it, the last of them will say: "Our Lord! Our Lord has led us astray." He will say: "Our Lord, He has led us astray, so the torment of the Fire will come upon us." He will say: "This is the punishment of each other, but you do not know."
And the first of them will say to the last of them: "You are not arrogant over us, so taste the punishment for what you used to earn."
As for those who reject Our signs and do not turn away from them, the gates of heaven will not be opened, nor will they enter the Garden until the camel comes through the eye of the needle, and thus do We recompense the guilty.
They will have a bed of fire, and coverings above them. Thus do We recompense the unjust.
And as for those who believe and do good works, We do not burden any soul beyond its scope; these are the dwellers of the Garden; they shall abide therein forever.
And We will remove from them what is in their hearts, and rivers flow beneath them, and they will say, "Praise be to Allah, Who has guided us to us. Had Allah not guided us, we would not have been guided in the way of our Lord." And the Messenger of Our Lord has come to the truth, and they will be called to the right place.
And the dwellers of the Garden will call out to the companions of the Fire (saying): "We have indeed found that which our Lord promised us to be true. Have you found what your Lord promised you to be true?" They will say: "Yes, the curse of Allah is upon the wrongdoers."
Those who bar from the way of Allah and seek to make it crooked, and they are not in the Hereafter.
And there shall be a barrier between them, and the dwellers of the heights will know that they will recognize their marks by their marks, and they will call out to the dwellers of the Garden: "Peace be with you." They will not enter therein, but they will be in a state of peace.
